          <long_desc isprivate="0">
            <who name="Enrico Persiani">enrico@ninfea-soft.org</who>
            <bug_when>2006-06-08 04:33:37 EDT</bug_when>
            <thetext>This patch allows to specify multiple ntlm server authenticators using a comma
separated list of servers in the ntlm_server option, as in the following example:

ntlm_server: server1, server2, .., serverN

This feture has both the advantages to enable fault tolerance with ntlm server 
replicas and to allow authentication with different ntlm servers.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
